title: Vashon/Fauntleroy/Southworth ferry riders should expect delays
text:
Ferry riders should expect delays today if they travel the Vashon/Fauntleroy/Southworth run.
The ferry Issaquah has been pulled from service for repairs.
The Salish is filling in, but is a smaller boat. That means each run will have 500 fewer passengers and 60 fewer cars.
This is the second time in the last week the ferry Issaquah has been pulled for repairs.
